<TITLE> Poet Samudra Gupta dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 19 (bdnews24.com)  Poet Samudra Gupta died in hospital in India Saturday at the age of 62, his daughter said. Gupta died at Narayana Hrudayalaya Hospital around 8am, the poet's younger daughter Swapna Samudra told bdnews24.com. The ailing poet was taken to India on July 3 for better medical treatment. Swapna said the poet's wife and brother, who accompanied him to India, would bring the body back home. Gupta was admitted to BIRDEM Hospital on May 10. He was first diagnosed with a blockage in the gallbladder. He was later transferred to Square Hospital. The poet was then taken to Narayana Hrudayalaya Hospital in Bangalore where doctors detected a tumour near his liver, which turned cancerous. The poet had also suffered from high-blood pressure and diabetes, his daughter said. The poet's friends, poets and well-wishers flocked to his home after the news of his death spread. Gupta was born in Hasil village of Sirajganj on June 23, 1946. He wrote poems, stories, articles and newspaper columns. bdnews
